The paper proposes a novel learning method for deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) that is biologically motivated. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). The method is evaluated using image discrimination tasks, indicating that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV). The paper proposes a pre-training method for CNNs that utilizes unsupervised competitive learning, which could be considered a form of reinforcement learning, suggesting that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper suggests that the proposed method could be useful for a variety of poorly labeled data, such as medical data, indicating that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL).
